MISSION ORTLER RONDA IN 1 DAY 🥵

Last week, I tried to complete this epic Enduro tour by the day. It involved 4 passes above 3.000m + the climb of Passo Stelvio, 1 glacier crossing with crampons, 4.900 vertical meters and 5 mind-blowing descents. All surrounded by the unique mountain and glacier landscapes of the Ortler-Cevedale massif. This tour usually takes 3 to 4 days.
To complete it in 1 day, was a dream I had been cherishing since last year when I completed the tour in 2 days. This year, I decided to attempt it alone and in the lightest possible way.
The following is the story of a somewhat crazy idea that turned into an incredible journey:

I started at 04.45 am from the II. cantoniera on the Bormio side of the Passo Stelvio road. At 05.45 I reached the pass and shortly after, I started the descent along the legendary Tibet Trail with the first light of the rising sun. From Gomagoi to Sulden, I had to climb approx 700 vertical meters along the main road. Once in Sulden I took the lift up to the Schaubachhütte. From this point I cycled uphill until the Madritschjoch at 3.123m where I arrived at 09.30. This marks the beginning of the epic Madritsch-Trail down to the Zufallhütte, almost 1.000 downhill meters of pure joy! From here, it's an endless and challenging ascent to Rifugio Casati at 3.254m. In the last section of the uphill, I had to wear crampons and carry my bike over a glacier. I reached the highest point of the Ortler Ronda tour at 13.15. A short break to eat 2 energy bars and then I started the descent down to Rifugio Pizzini, where I loaded the bike on my shoulders again to hike up the Passo Zebrù at 3.005m (arrival at 14.30). The following descent down to the Zebrù valley was mind-blowing! 

I reached Niblogo at 15.30. This is the starting point of the old military road up to Passo Ables (3.012 m). There were still 1.450m to climb and a technical descent along a WWI trail to reach my car and complete the Ortler Ronda. I still had 5 hours of daylight and in case my headlamp: I was tired but super pumped to go on!

Mission completed! 🇲🇦⛰️⛰️
Last week, together with the strong @alpistour crew from Slovakia, we have summited and descended by bike the 2 highest summits of #Morocco:
⛰️ Jbel Toubkal, 4.167m

It was the first ever commercial biking expedition of this kind, combining the descent of these 2 summits.
Chapeau to all the participants and thanks for the great time!👊🙏
